There are several categories of individuals who are entitled to Irish citizenship based on where they were born and whether any of their parents held Irish citizenship. The categories are:

* Individuals born in Ireland or Northern Ireland before Jan 1, 2005;
* Individuals born in Ireland or Northern Ireland after Dec 31, 2004, whose parents meet certain citizenship requirements;
* Individuals born outside of Ireland, whose parents or grandparents hold/held Irish citizenship or were registered on the Foreign Births Register;
* Individuals born in Ireland and who are not citizens of any other country.

